                    <msContents>
                        <summary> An incomplete manuscript entitled <title type="main" xml:lang="ja"
                                source="IANA">痘疹精要</title> | <title type="alt" xml:lang="ja-Latn"
                                source="IANA">Toshin seiyo</title> | <title type="alt" xml:lang="en"
                                source="IANA">The essentials of smallpox</title>, including coloured
                            illustrations of different symptoms of smallpox. An inscription on the
                            title page of the second volume attributes the work to <persName
                                type="aut" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">神田玄泉</persName> | <persName
                                type="aut" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Kanda, Gensen</persName>
                            <date>(c.1670-1746)</date> with revisions and supplements by <persName
                                xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">榎本玄昌新</persName> | <persName
                                xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Enomoto, Gensho</persName>, a
                            doctor in <placeName>Kiyomizu</placeName> domain (modern
                                <placeName>Gifu</placeName> Prefecture). </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_63">

                            <author key="person_259185764" source="VIAF">
                                <persName xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">神田 玄泉</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Kanda, Gensen</persName>
                                <note><p>Gensen produced a number of illustrated albums on subjects
                                        such as fishes, whaling, materia medica and a couple of
                                        medical works including a study of dietetics. Many of these
                                        works survive in a number of copies, although none were
                                        published, suggesting that he was deliberately avoiding
                                        publication and restricting circulation to his
                                        followers.</p></note>
                            </author>

                            <title>
                                <title type="main" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">痘疹精要</title>
                                <title type="alt" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Toshin
                                    seiyo</title>
                                <title type="alt" xml:lang="en" source="IANA">The essentials of
                                    smallpox</title>
                            </title>

                            <filiation><p>There does not appear to be any record of a manuscript
                                    with this title in Japan, though there are records of a work by
                                    him bearing a similar title, <title xml:lang="ja" source="IANA"
                                        >痘疹口訣</title> | <title xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA"
                                        >Tōshin kuketsu</title>, in collections that are now
                                    lost</p></filiation>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>

